The function checking whether a given string is a palindrome is in:
server/routes/palindrome.js

To run the mongo daemon, use the following command from the root directory:
mongod --dbpath ./db --port 27018

To run the server, first cd into the server folder and run npm install.
Then use:
node server

To run the client app, cd into client and run npm install here, too.
Then you can use:
npm start
or
ng serve --o
to automatically open the browser window.

To run the unit tests, cd into client and run the following:
ng test
